[[File:The_White_Elephant,_Punch_103.png|thumb]]在1892年[[内战|内战]]爆发后成为[[不列颠东非公司|不列颠东非公司]]的“白象”。]]

在[[现代|现代]]的用法中，白象指那些消耗龐大[[資源|資源]]卻[[无用|无用]]或无[[价值|价值]]的[[物体|物体]]、[[计划|计划]]、[[商业|商业]][[风险|风险]]或[[公共设施|公共设施]]等 <ref>{{cite web|url = http://oxforddictionaries.com/definition/english/white%2Belephant|title = Home : Oxford English Dictionary|publisher = oxforddictionaries.com|accessdate = 25 April 2013|archive-date = 2016-05-02|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160502205508/http://www.oxforddictionaries.com/definition/english/white+elephant|dead-url = no}}</ref>。一些[[價錢|造價]]昂貴但沒有實際[[效能|效用]]，或成本過高但回報少的[[工程|工程]]項目都可能被形容為「白象工程」<ref>{{cite web |author1=周顯 |title=甚麼是大白象工程？ |url=https://www.am730.com.hk/column/%E8%B2%A1%E7%B6%93/%E7%94%9A%E9%BA%BC%E6%98%AF%E5%A4%A7%E7%99%BD%E8%B1%A1%E5%B7%A5%E7%A8%8B%EF%BC%9F-111356 |website=am730 |accessdate=2018-07-02 |language=zh-hk |date=2018-01-12 |archive-date=2019-06-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190610145201/https://www.am730.com.hk/column/%E8%B2%A1%E7%B6%93/%E7%94%9A%E9%BA%BC%E6%98%AF%E5%A4%A7%E7%99%BD%E8%B1%A1%E5%B7%A5%E7%A8%8B%EF%BC%9F-111356 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

== 背景 ==
[[File:Lord_White_Elephant.jpg|thumb]]宫殿的白象。]]
此词源于[[缅甸|缅甸]]、[[泰国|泰国]]、[[老挝|老挝]]和[[柬埔寨|柬埔寨]]这些东南亚君主所供养的神圣白象<ref>[http://www.thailandelephant.org/en/royalstable.html "Royal Elephant Stable"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.thailandelephant.org/en/royalstable.html |date=20210309020106 }}.</ref>。拥有白象，曾被视为（且在泰国和缅甸现在依旧如此）君主统治[[公平正义|公平正义]]与其[[权力|权力]]的象征，也是王国和平与繁荣的象征。君主常常在他们正式的头衔中显示他们拥有白象，如[[贡榜王朝|贡榜王朝]]的第三位君主[[辛标信|辛标信]]自号“白象王”<ref name="leider">{{cite journal|last = Leider|first = Jacques P.|date = December 2011|title = A Kingship by Merit and Cosmic Investiture|journal = Journal of Burma Studies|volume = 15|issue = 2|url = http://muse.jhu.edu/journals/journal_of_burma_studies/v015/15.2.leider.html}}</ref>。

白象与[[印度教|印度教]][[宇宙论|宇宙论]]有关联：[[因陀罗|因陀罗]]的坐骑艾拉瓦塔是一头白象。白象也与[[佛教|佛教]]的[[大千世界|大千世界]]有着错综复杂的联系：[[帝释天|帝释天]]的坐骑是一只名为艾拉瓦塔的三头白象<ref name="leider">{{cite journal|last = Leider|first = Jacques P.|date = December 2011|title = A Kingship by Merit and Cosmic Investiture|journal = Journal of Burma Studies|volume = 15|issue = 2|url = http://muse.jhu.edu/journals/journal_of_burma_studies/v015/15.2.leider.html}}</ref>。真正的白化大象在自然界中，通常是红褐色或粉红色<ref>{{cite news|last = Morelle|first = Rebecca|url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/sci/tech/7951331.stm|title = Science & Environment | Pink elephant is caught on camera|publisher = BBC News|date = 20 March 2009|accessdate = 14 March 2013|archive-date = 2017-08-14|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170814093046/http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/sci/tech/7951331.stm|dead-url = no}}</ref>。

这些说法源自佛陀诞生和白象的故事。相传在佛陀出生前，他的母亲梦见白象赠送代表智慧和纯洁的莲花给她<ref>{{cite web|url = http://kadampa.org/en/reference/the-birth-of-buddha/|title = The Birth of Buddha | The New Kadampa Tradition (ºla)|publisher = Kadampa.org|accessdate = 14 April 2011|deadurl = yes|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110326115609/http://kadampa.org/en/reference/the-birth-of-buddha/|archivedate = 2011年3月26日}}</ref>。因为白象被认为是神圣的，并且法律保护白象免受劳作，因而收到君主赠与的白象是福亦是祸。福是因为动物是神圣的而且是君主恩惠的象征；祸则是因为接受者不仅要花费一笔高昂的饲养费，而且还不能转赠他人或将之投入实际的使用中。

由泰国政府颁发的[[白象勳章|白象勋章]]包含八个等级。尼泊尔也有白象。

在西方，“白象”一词指花费昂贵但又没有达到预期目的物品。这一词语因[[費尼爾司·泰勒·巴納姆|費尼爾司·泰勒·巴納姆]]的经历而为人所知。巴納姆曾购入一只名为Toung Taloung的“神圣缅甸白象”。在付出巨大的努力和高昂的花费后，巴納姆终于获得了来自暹罗国王的动物，却发现他的“白象”的颜色实际上是有一些粉色斑点的脏灰色<ref>{{cite book|last1 = Harding|first1 = Les|title = Elephant Story: Jumbo and P.T. Barnum Under the Big Top|date = 1999|publisher = McFarland|location = Jefferson, N.C.|isbn = 0786406321|page = 110|url = http://books.google.com/books?id=iDllhLZcF0IC&pg=PA110#v=onepage&q&f=false|access-date = 2015-07-16|archive-date = 2017-02-01|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170201080203/https://books.google.com/books?id=iDllhLZcF0IC&pg=PA110#v=onepage&q&f=false|dead-url = no}}</ref>。

“白象”和“白象礼物”这些词语在十九世纪中叶开始广泛使用<ref>{{cite web|last1 = Brown|first1 = Peter Jensen|title = Two-and-a-half Idioms - the History and Etymology of "White Elephants"|url = http://esnpc.blogspot.com/2014/06/two-and-half-idioms-history-and.html|website = Early Sports 'n' Pop-Culture History Blog|accessdate = 25 June 2014|archive-date = 2021-03-01|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210301021211/https://esnpc.blogspot.com/2014/06/two-and-half-idioms-history-and.html|dead-url = no}}</ref>。在二十世纪初期，这个用法通常以“白象交换”和“白象销售”的形式出现<ref>{{cite web|last1 = Brown|first1 = Peter Jensen|title = Two-and-a-Half More Idioms - "White Elephants" and Yankee Swaps|url = http://esnpc.blogspot.com/2014/06/two-and-half-more-idioms-white.html|website = Early Sports 'n' Pop-Culture History Blog|accessdate = 3 July 2014|archive-date = 2020-11-08|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201108110506/https://esnpc.blogspot.com/2014/06/two-and-half-more-idioms-white.html|dead-url = no}}</ref>。许多教会集市进行“白象销售”，在那里捐赠者可以将自己不需要的小古董出售以获取利润，因为一个人的垃圾是另一个人的宝贝。许多组织和教会集市今天仍在使用这个词。一般来说，“白象”通常指一个毫无用处、但可能昂贵而又古怪的物品。

